<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{nisuru}}}} usually follows a noun although it can follow a noun plus particle.
</p>

<p>
If the tense is nonpast it implies that the decision has just been taken. If it is past, then it is ambiguous
as to whether the decision has yet been enacted.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{ni kimeru}} has the same meaning and can be used interchangeably with @HI{{@EM{{nisuru}}}}, although @HI{{ni kimeru}}
is usually used only when the decision is considered to be important.
</p>

